## How to connect order processing automation to Sage

The integration between an AI order processing tool and Sage works as an intake layer. The flow:

1. Customer email arrives at your monitored inbox
2. AI reads and interprets the order (any format)
3. AI matches products to your Sage catalog
4. High-confidence orders push to Sage via API as new sales orders
5. Flagged items appear in review dashboard for human confirmation
6. Confirmed items push to Sage
7. Sage sends confirmation data back to the AI, which triggers customer confirmation

For Sage 200 and Sage Business Cloud, this uses the standard Sage REST API for sales order creation. The same endpoint accepts orders from any source. For [ERP order integration](/insights/erp-order-integration-automation) details including API architecture and IT setup requirements, that guide covers the technical implementation.

IT involvement for a standard Sage integration is typically five to ten hours for setup and under one hour per month for maintenance.

